inuierliche Experimentieren der Künstler mit dem ästhetischen Leistungsvermögen des Mediums offen.  aThe study analyzes differentiated concepts of truth in Dutch prints of the 16th and 17th centuries. Against the backdrop of religious and political crises of the time, it elaborates on how copperplate engravings and etchings not only represent veritas but, by problematizing their own medial status, reflect on visual forms of evidence generation and art’s specific capacity for truth.  aIssued also in print.  afunded by Sonderforschungsbereich 1391 Andere Ästhetik  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aDruckgraphik. 4aFrühe Neuzeit. 4aNiederlande. 4aWahrheit. 7aART / European.2bisacsh  aGraphic reproduction.  aNetherlands.  aearly modern era.  atruth.2 aSonderforschungsbereich 1391 Andere Ästhetikefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2023z9783111318103oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG0 cEPUBz97831111244900 cprintz978311112253340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311112300440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111123004423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111123004/original  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DPKb2023